title: Start
---
$c1: Hey. You look like you've got somewhere to be. That usually means you want something first.

$c1: Before I start naming prices, I'm deciding whether you're trouble, broke, or both.
-> $c2: What are you selling?
    $c1: Depends on who's asking. For someone with your gear-probably nothing you can't use.
    $c1: Meds. Charge cells. Couple of data shards I probably shouldn't have. Take your pick.
    <<jump Trade>>
-> $c2: Just passing through.
    $c1: Sure you are. Everyone's just passing through. Nobody stops here on purpose.
    $c1: You want the bypass route or not? Twenty chips and I'll save you twenty minutes.
    <<jump Route>>
-> $c2: You seen anyone unusual in this block?
    $c1: Define unusual. Round here that bar is pretty low.
    $c1: Though-yeah. Corporate types. Not Redline. Different logo. Moving fast, not talking to anyone.
    <<jump Intel>>
===
title: Trade
---
$c1: I've got stim patches and a trauma injector. Both marked, both functional. The injector's sealed-you'd know if it wasn't.

-> $c2: I'll take the stim patch.
    $c1: Good call. Don't use it unless you mean it-crash comes fast on these.
    <<jump Close>>
-> $c2: What about the data shards?
    $c1: That one's not for everyone. You'd need to know what to do with it, and you'd need to want the trouble.
    $c1: Still interested?
    -> $c2: Yes.
        $c1: Then find me later. Not here. Too many ears on this corner right now.
        <<jump Close>>
    -> $c2: No, I'll pass.
        $c1: Smart. Buy a stim patch instead. Safer hobby.
        <<jump Close>>
===
title: Route
---
$c1: East service tunnel. Access panel behind the dumpster stack-code's been the same for three years, nobody cares.

$c1: Avoids the checkpoint and the flooded corridor. Gets you to the atrium level in under five minutes.

-> $c2: Thanks.
    $c1: Don't mention it. Literally. I mean that.
    <<jump Close>>
===
title: Intel
---
$c1: They were moving a container. Medium size, sealed, two handles. Looked heavy for its size.

$c1: I don't know what's in it and I don't want to. But they headed toward the subfloor access. Third building east.

-> $c2: That's useful.
    $c1: Most things I say are. Most people just don't stick around to hear them.
    <<jump Close>>
===
title: Close
---
$c1: Stay sharp. This block gets weird after dark and it's already getting weird.
===
